description: Deletes the specified transit gateway route table. If there are any route tables associated with the transit gateway route table, you must first run  DisassociateRouteTable before you can delete the transit gateway route table. This removes any route tables associated with the transit gateway route table.

parameters.name: TransitGatewayRouteTableId
parameters.description: The ID of the transit gateway route table.

nested_items.name: TransitGatewayRouteTable
nested_items.description: Information about the deleted transit gateway route table.

nested_items.description: The ID of the transit gateway route table.

nested_items.name: TransitGatewayId

nested_items.name: DefaultAssociationRouteTable
nested_items.description: Indicates whether this is the default association route table for the transit gateway.

nested_items.description: Indicates whether this is the default propagation route table for the transit gateway.

nested_items.description: Any tags assigned to the route table.
